  "prompt": "What should I do to get into IIT?",
  "response": "To get into an IIT (Indian Institute of Technology), you'll need to follow these steps:\n\n1. Academic Preparation\n- Study hard in 11th and 12th, focusing on Physics, Chemistry, and Mathematics\n- Maintain a high percentage in board exams\n- Focus on building strong fundamentals in science and math\n\n2. JEE Preparation\n- Appear for JEE Main exam (first stage)\n- Qualify for JEE Advanced (top 2.5 lakh candidates)\n- Start preparing early, ideally from 11th standard\n- Join coaching classes or use online study materials\n- Practice previous years' question papers\n- Take regular mock tests\n\n3. Study Strategy\n- Create a structured study plan\n- Cover entire JEE syllabus\n- Focus on concept understanding, not just memorization\n- Practice problem-solving\n- Time management is crucial\n\n4. Additional Recommendations\n- Solve NCERT textbooks thoroughly\n- Use reference books by renowned authors\n- Develop strong problem-solving skills\n- Stay mentally and physically healthy\n- Manage stress effectively\n\n5. Entrance Exam Tips\n- Understand exam pattern\n- Work on speed and accuracy\n- Learn time management\n- Stay calm during the exam\n\nRemember, consistent hard work and smart preparation are key to cracking JEE and getting into IIT.",
